<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-79-0869 </DOCNO><TEXT>The daily operation of the gas measurement laboratory function has changedconsiderably in the last five years at the Southern California Gas Company.Gas measurement laboratories no longer look like laboratories. Todaythey can be more accurately described as gas analysis centers containingelectronic equipment and multiple computer terminals. The major emphasisof this paper is to describe the computerized Gas Quality MeasurementSystem (GQMS) in operation at the author's measurement gas analysis centers.The daily function of a gas analysis center, from the collection of asample cylinder to the analysis of a gas sample by a measurement technician,will also be described to illustrate the flow of information from thefield to GQMS to their Measurement Office.</TEXT></DOC>